author: COMSOL
description:
This example explores the convective flow effects in a cell with a rotating wafer. Electrolyte enters the cell from the bottom and flows toward the rotating wafer where copper is deposited. The laminar flow profile, the concentration of copper, the electrolyte potential and the electric potential of the thin wafer is solved for.

The geometry is made in two dimensions with axial symmetry.

This model requires the Electrodeposition Module and the CFD Module.
